riest in the Episcopal Church after graduation."},{"institution":"Indiana University","degree":"M.A. Adult Education","year_completed":1967,"notes":"Master's in Adult Education."},{"institution":"Indiana University","degree":"M.A. Political Science","year_completed":1968,"notes":"Master's in Political Science."},{"institution":"Indiana University","degree":"Ed.D. / Ph.D. Education and Political Science","year_completed":1969,"notes":"Doctorate in Education and Political Science."}],"career":[{"title":"Episcopal Priest","organization":"Diocese of Chicago, Episcopal Church","dates":"1950-1966 (and ongoing as supply priest after 1981)","type":"religion","notes":"Ordained 1950 after Seabury-Western Seminary B.D. Served on multiple diocesan committees, boards, and councils."},{"title":"Priest-in-Charge then Rector, St. Giles Church","organization":"St. Giles Episcopal Church, Northbrook IL","dates":"1950-1966","type":"religion","notes":"Began ministry as Priest-in-Charge; later appointed Rector."},{"title":"Dean of Ohio University Chillicothe Campus","organization":"Ohio University Chillicothe Branch","dates":"1969-1981","type":"education","notes":"Headed the Chillicothe regional campus for 12 years following Indiana University doctorate."},{"title":"Supply priest","organization":"St. Paul's Episcopal Church Chillicothe and other Diocese of Southern Ohio parishes","dates":"1981+","type":"religion","notes":"Continued as supply priest in retirement."}],"military_service":[{"service":"U.S. Army Air Corps","branch":"USAAF","dates":"1942-1946","conflict":"World War II","rank":"Major (retired)","notes":"22 months in the Western Pacific combat area. LANDED ON IWO JIMA on the FIFTH DAY of the battle (one of the bloodiest of the Pacific Theater). Retired as Major in 1946."}],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"tags":["wwii","minister","clergy","episcopal","educator"],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[{"type":"military","related_id":"HD3752","display_label":"Cousin who died nursing for France in WWI","link_text":"Josephine Redding"},{"type":"naming_pattern","related_id":"HD3711","display_label":"Cleveland Leader publisher granduncle, his Edwin namesake","link_text":"Edwin Cowles"}],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"military","header":"Iwo Jima on the fifth day of battle","body":"A US Army Air Corps officer, Edwin Jr. spent twenty-two months in the Western Pacific combat area during World War II. He landed on Iwo Jima on the fifth day of the battle — one of the bloodiest engagements of the Pacific Theater — and retired in 1946 with the rank of Major."},{"number":2,"category":"religion","header":"Episcopal priest at St. Giles Northbrook 1950-1966","body":"After Seabury-Western Theological Seminary in 1950, Edwin Jr. was ordained as an Episcopal priest in the Diocese of Chicago. He served as Priest-in-Charge then Rector at St. Giles Church in Northbrook IL from 1950 through 1966 — sixteen years at one parish — and on numerous diocesan committees and councils."},{"number":3,"category":"education","header":"Dean of Ohio University Chillicothe 1969-1981","body":"After three Indiana University degrees in adult education and political science, culminating in a 1969 doctorate, Edwin Jr. headed Ohio University's Chillicothe regional campus as Dean for twelve years. He continued as a supply priest in the Diocese of Southern Ohio after retiring."},{"number":4,"category":"character","header":"Eagle Scout and Silver Beaver Award honoree","body":"A lifelong Boy Scouts of America supporter, Edwin Jr. attained the rank of Eagle Scout and was later presented with the Silver Beaver Award for his service to the Chief Logan Council. He was also a Paul Harris Fellow of Rotary International through the Chillicothe Rotary Club."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"edwin-badger-jr-1916"},"I00419":{"id":"I00419","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":f